INSERT INTO `learn` (`class`, `h3`, `p`, `id`, `related_posts`, `html`, `image_name`, `meta`) VALUES
('fa-wallet', 'Crypto wallets & Crypto Exchanges', 'Learn about differences of crypto wallets.', 1, 'wallet', '    <br>\r\n    <h2>Crypto exchanges</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>If you have crypto on exchanges, you don\'t own that money. You are paying company to hold your crypto, it\'s not yours. </p>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <li>Governments may have the authority to freeze or seize assets belonging to exchanges that operate within their jurisdiction.</li>\r\n    <li>You may be at risk of tax theft, asset forfeiture theft, and civil theft.</li>\r\n    <li>You may be at risk of exit theft.</li>\r\n    <li>You make job for black hat hackers easy</li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>\r\n        Cryptocurrency security is a top concern for many investors, especially when it comes to protecting their digital \r\n        assets through the use of a crypto wallet. But with so many options available, it can be tough to determine which \r\n        wallets offer the highest level of security. In this article, we\'ll provide an overview of some of the most secure \r\n        crypto wallets currently on the market, as well as offer tips for selecting the safest option for your needs. \r\n        Remember, the ultimate security of your crypto wallet depends on how you manage it, so be sure to consider \r\n        all the factors that go into keeping your assets safe.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Storing crypto on exchanges, banks, or web wallets can be risky and can contribute to the centralization of the crypto \r\n        ecosystem. This can lead to increased security vulnerabilities and reduced decentralization of the network. Instead, \r\n        it is generally considered more secure to store your crypto in a personal wallet that you control, such as a hardware wallet.\r\n        This allows you to maintain control over your private keys, which are necessary to access \r\n        and use your crypto. By keeping your crypto in a personal wallet, you can help ensure the security of your \r\n        assets and contribute to the overall security and decentralization of the crypto network.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        When you download a cryptocurrency wallet, you may be prompted to get your seed keys. \r\n        These keys are displayed on the screen for you to read. However, you should be aware that your phone may have been \r\n        exposed to malicious sites or apps, which could have infected your device with malware. Many people\'s devices \r\n        are infected with malware, and someone may be able to use a key logger to watch your activity through the \r\n        infected software. Therefore, it\'s important to be cautious when downloading mainstream wallets, as your screen may \r\n        be captured as soon as you download or run the wallet.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <h2>On a cryptocurrency exchange, you don\'t have control over your own digital assets.</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <h3>Organizations such as Coinbase and Visa have implemented measures to block Russian citizens from accessing their services.</h3>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>Message from Coinbase:</p>\r\n    <b>â€žImportant: Action required by May 31, 2022 to avoid losing access to your Coinbase account. To comply with EU sanctions that prohibit Coinbase from providing crypto services to certain Russian customers, Coinbase will soon restrict your ability to access your account. Before May 31, 2022, you need to withdraw all funds from your account or provide us with specific documents to show you are not covered by these sanctions. After that date you risk your funds being frozen. Additional funds sent to your Coinbase account during this time period may also be frozen.</b>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <h2>Solution</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <li>Use hardware wallets</li>\r\n    <li>Dont use Crypto Exchanges</li>\r\n    <li>Use seperate, clean device only for crypto</li>\r\n    <li>Don\'t use public WIFI</li>\r\n    <li>Change your password regularly</li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>\r\n        The only current way to secure your crypto is to store it in a hardware wallet, I personally use both Trezor and Ledger\r\n        I suggest that you get ones without Bluetooth because the most time-consuming and difficult aspect of hacking a device\r\n        is often the information-gathering and planning stages. By reducing the attack surface device has, \r\n        you make it more difficult for attackers to gain access.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        I use Trezor and Ledger hardware wallets because they provide an extra layer of security for my cryptocurrency. \r\n        When you first create a wallet on a hardware device, it generates a seed key, which is a list of \r\n        random words that are displayed on the device\'s screen. This ensures that no hacker can access the key, \r\n        as it is not stored on your smartphone or computer. It\'s important to write down the seed key and \r\n        store it in a secure, location, possibly in multiple pieces, to ensure the safety \r\n        of your crypto assets. Using a hardware wallet is a smart way to store cryptocurrency. Quite opposite of crypto exchanges.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <br>', '1.webp', 'Storing crypto on exchanges, banks, or web wallets can be risky and contribute to centralization. This can lead to security vulnerabilities and reduced decentralization of the network.'),
('fa-medal', 'Best Privacy Coin', 'Privacy coins are undervalued in the cryptocurrency space.', 2, 'best', ' <h2>Monero</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>\r\n        Monero is a popular privacy coin that allows users to conduct digital transactions privately and anonymously.\r\n        Unlike Bitcoin, which is often perceived as anonymous and untraceable, Monero actually has these features. \r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Bitcoin is no longer anonymous because individuals are linking their identities to their Bitcoin transactions through exchanges. \r\n        When a person uploads their identification to an exchange and uses it to purchase Bitcoin, their identity becomes permanently \r\n        associated with that specific coin.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Monero is not widely available on exchanges, which is where many normies typically \r\n        purchase their coins. Additionally, institutions tend to avoid Monero due to its potential association with \r\n        illegal activities and the risk of scrutiny from government agencies such as the IRS. There is significant \r\n        institutional resistance to Monero, and it has been banned in some locations and may be banned in others in the future. \r\n        The media often portrays Monero as being connected with terrorism and crime, similar to how Bitcoin was once perceived.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n        Monero was designed with technology that allows it to operate on the blockchain without revealing users\r\n        wallet addresses or transaction amounts. It also has a built-in mixer function, similar to those used for Bitcoin. \r\n        Monero\'s strong privacy features have attracted the attention of government agencies such as the IRS, which \r\n        has offered a $625,000 bounty for anyone who can develop a method for tracing Monero transactions.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <strong>\r\n        Despite this, Monero remains a highly secure and private cryptocurrency option, making it ideal for \r\n        users who want to protect their financial transactions from being monitored.\r\n    </strong>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>\r\n        An example of the privacy provided by the traditional banking system is the ability to transfer money to a \r\n        friend without revealing how much each person has. In contrast, using cryptocurrencies like BTC, ETH, \r\n        or others (excluding Monero) would allow both parties to see each other\'s balances, as well as the amount \r\n        of cryptocurrency being sent or received. This lack of privacy makes it unlikely that any cryptocurrency \r\n        will be able to replace fiat, unless it can offer better privacy protection than fiat. Monero addresses \r\n        this issue by providing stronger privacy features.\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>I am a big fan of Monero because of its commitment to freedom and privacy. I believe it has a bright future and will do everything I can to support it</p>\r\n    <br>', '2.webp', 'Monero is a privacy coin that allows users to conduct private and anonymous digital transactions.'),
('fa-person-circle-question', 'Who Accepts Crypto as Payment?', 'Businesses and organizations that accept cryptocurrency as payment.', 3, 'info', '<br>\r\n        <br>\r\n        <h2>\r\n            Cryptocurrency has gained widespread adoption and is now accepted by numerous large companies as a \r\n            legitimate form of payment. In this Page, we will attempt to provide an overview of all the companies that accept cryptocurrency.\r\n        </h2>\r\n\r\n        <br>\r\n\r\n\r\n        <div class=\"whoacceptscrypto-li\">\r\n            <strong><li>Newsgroup.Ninja</li></strong> <p> - Tier-1 Usenet reseller intent on providing superior service at a low price.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Astraweb</li></strong> <p> - Astraweb is a Usenet/newsgroup service provider.</p> \r\n            <strong><li>Blocknews</li></strong> <p> - BlockNews is a a Usenet servive provider that has servers in the US.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Old Fitzroy</li></strong> <p> - The Old Fitzroy is a pub, bistro and theatre all rolled into one.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>The Pink Cow</li></strong> <p> - The Pink Cow California-Mexican Restaurant & Bar.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Zynga</li></strong> <p> - Free Mobile & Online Games.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>EZTV</li></strong> <p> - Most visited torrent site for TV shows.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Suntimes</li></strong> <p> - The Chicago Sun-Times is a daily newspaper published in Chicago, Illinois.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Bitcoin.Travel</li></strong> <p> - Book your travel with bitcoins and other cryptocurrencies.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Humblebundle</li></strong> <p> - Digital storefront for video games.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>BigFishGames</li></strong> <p> -  Casual gaming company based in Seattle, with a regional office in Oakland, California.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Euro Pacific</li></strong> <p> - An online, international bank designed for global individuals and companies.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Travala</li></strong> <p> - Book Hotels, Flights, Tours & Activities.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Pembury Tavern</li></strong> <p> - Legendary East London community boozer serving pints and Hackney locals since 1856.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>The Libertarian Party</li></strong> <p> - Political party in the United States that promotes civil liberties.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Yacht-base</li></strong> <p> - Wide selection of both luxury and budget sailing and motor boats.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Etsy</li></strong> <p> - Global online marketplace, where people come together to make, sell, buy, and collect unique items.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>PizzaForCoins</li></strong> <p> - Order Pizza With Bitcoins.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Bitcoincoffee</li></strong> <p> - This unique project combines a cafÃ© and coworking space where the only method of payment is Bitcoin virtual currency.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Newsdemon</li></strong> <p> - Provides the fastest USENET access whether you have a 5Mbps or 1000Mbps connection.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Straub Auto Repairs</li></strong> <p> - Auto repair shop in Hastings-on-Hudson, New York.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Hitnews</li></strong> <p> - Providing access to usenet for 20 years. A suitable package for every internet user.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>StingyUsenet</li></strong> <p> - No-nonsense Usenet provider.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Coupa CafÃ©</li></strong> <p> - Family owned business founded in Downtown Palo Alto in 2004.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>PureVPN</li></strong> <p> - PureVPN is a commercial VPN service owned by GZ Systems Ltd. Founded in 2007, the company is based in the British Virgin Islands.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>That\'s my face</li></strong> <p> - Custom action figures, dolls and lifelike masks from any portrait photo.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Foodler </li></strong> <p> - American online food ordering service that connected consumers with a wide variety of restaurants for immediate delivery.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Amagi Metals</li></strong> <p> - Buy silver bullion, coins, bars and rounds through our secure ordering system today!</p>\r\n            <strong><li>theCubenet</li></strong> <p> - Secure and Reliable Usenet and VPN Service.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>SFU bookstore</li></strong> <p> - SFU\'s Bookstore & Spirit Shop serving our university community.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>NewsgroupDirect</li></strong> <p> - Independent Usenet Provider. Free posting and headers.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>UsenetExpress</li></strong> <p> - UsenetExpress uses 2048-Bit SSL certificates for our encrypted connections providing the most secure connection in the industry.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>UsenetPrime</li></strong> <p> - Internet service provider in Duncan, South Carolina.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Cheapnews</li></strong> <p> - Usenet provider Cheapnews is a Usenet payserver.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Mollie</li></strong> <p> - Finance industry pioneer and one of Europe\'s fastest-growing fintechs.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Rakuten</li></strong> <p> - Rakuten Group, Inc. is a Japanese technology conglomerate based in Tokyo, founded by Hiroshi Mikitani in 1997.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Badoo</li></strong> <p> - Badoo is a dating-focused social network founded by Russian entrepreneur Andrey Andreev in 2006.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Intuit</li></strong> <p> - American business software company that specializes in financial software.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>MovieTickets.com</li></strong> <p> - Online movie ticketing website founded by AMC Theatres and Hollywood.com.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>ShopJoy</li></strong> <p> - Get all the rad skate gear for you or the shredder in your life.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Dream Lover</li></strong> <p> - Dream Lover is a platform specializing in virtual relationships between users and professional models.</p>   \r\n            <strong><li>Alzashop</li></strong> <p> - Best shop and deals for electronics, computer technology and much more, with over 50000 different products in stock and ready for immediate delivery!</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Alternative Airlines</li></strong> <p> - Alternative Airlines is a unique global flight search and booking site.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Grass Hill Alpacas</li></strong> <p> - Raising alpacas on the gentle, scenic slopes of Grass Hill in Williamsburg, Massachusetts since 2006.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Lv.net</li></strong> <p> - Formerly LasVegas.Net was one of the first internet service providers in Las Vegas, in the early days of the internet.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Grooveshark</li></strong> <p> - Free Music Streaming/</p>\r\n            <strong><li>MIT Coop Store</li></strong> <p> - The Coop is not just the campus store, but it is deeply rooted in the tradition and the fabric of the Harvard and MIT communities.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>SimplePay</li></strong> <p> - Easy online payroll system.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Stripe</li></strong> <p> - Suite of APIs powering online payment processing and commerce solutions for internet businesses of all sizes.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>San Jose Earthquakes</li></strong> <p> - American professional soccer team based in San Jose, California.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Museum of the Coastal Bend</li></strong> <p> - Museum devoted to the region\'s heritage, from Spanish colonial artifacts to primitive hunting tools.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>JC Penney</li></strong> <p> - Midscale American department store chain operating 667 stores across 49 U.S. states and Puerto Rico.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Gap</li></strong> <p> - Commonly known as Gap Inc. or Gap, is an American worldwide clothing and accessories retailer.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>GameStop</li></strong> <p> - American video game, consumer electronics, and gaming merchandise retailer.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Fight for the Future</li></strong> <p> - Nonprofit advocacy group in the area of digital rights founded in 2011.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Curryupnow.com</li></strong> <p> - Offering Indian street food, in a fast casual setting with restaurants, food trucks, catering services and Mortar & Pestle bar.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Dish Network</li></strong> <p> - American television provider and the owner of the direct-broadcast satellite provider.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Helen\'s Pizza</li></strong> <p> - No-frills pizzeria with thick-crust slices & pies plus wings, pasta, hot & cold Italian heros.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Seoclerks</li></strong> <p> - The largest SEO Marketplace on the planet.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>State Republican Party</li></strong> <p> - The Republican Party, also commonly called the GOP is one of the two major contemporary political parties in the United States.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>mspinc.com</li></strong> <p> - Machine Solution Providers (MSP) designs and builds custom manufacturing equipment.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Shopify.com</li></strong> <p> - Canadian multinational e-commerce company headquartered in Ottawa, Ontario.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>WebJet</li></strong> <p> - imited is a global digital travel business operating in both consumer and wholesale markets.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>UsenetNews</li></strong> <p> - BEST independent Usenet servers.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>NewsgroupDirect</li></strong> <p> - Independent Usenet Provider. Free posting and headers. Unlimited access.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Green Man Gaming</li></strong> <p> - eCommerce portal from British-based online video game retailer, distributor and publisher, Green Man.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Save the Children</li></strong> <p> - Commonly known as Save the Children, is an international non-governmental organization established in the United Kingdom in 1919 to improve the lives of children.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Mexico\'s Universidad de las AmÃ©ricas Puebla</li></strong> <p> - Commonly known as UDLAP, is a Mexican private university located in San AndrÃ©s Cholula, near Puebla.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Famsa</li></strong> <p> - Retail company engaged in the purchase and sale of household appliances, electronic products, furniture, clothing and other consumer products in Mexico and United States.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Naughty America</li></strong> <p> - Adult stuff, don\'t look it up if you are under 18!</p>\r\n            <strong><li>RE/MAX London</li></strong> <p> - Global estate agency network that spreads across over 115 countries on six continents.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>T-Mobile Poland</li></strong> <p> - Polish mobile phone network operator.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>CEX</li></strong> <p> - British second hand retail store specialising in technology, computing, video games, DVDs and technology repair.</p>\r\n            <strong><li>Vipernews</li></strong> <p> - Premium Usenet access (also known as newsgroups) for a reasonable price all year round.</p>\r\n        </div>', '3.webp', 'Overview of companies that accept cryptocurrency as a form of payment.'),
('fa-triangle-exclamation', 'Common Crypto Scams', 'Scams often involve financial gain, and this is also true in the world of cryptocurrency.', 4, 'scams', '<h2>It can be helpful to be aware of the various types of scams that exist in the world of cryptocurrency. Some common types of cryptocurrency scams include:</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <ol>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>NTF</strong></li>\r\n        <p>NFT projects may be created with the sole purpose of generating profit for the creators without offering any real value to collectors or users. These types of projects may be seen as \"cash grabs,\" as they are primarily focused on generating revenue without providing any significant value or utility.</p>\r\n        \r\n        <li><strong>Phishing scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve tricking individuals into giving away their personal and financial information, such as login credentials or private keys, through fake websites or emails that appear to be legitimate.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Ponzi schemes</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve promising high returns on investment with little or no risk. They often rely on new investors to pay the returns of earlier investors, and eventually collapse when there are not enough new investors to sustain the scheme.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Investment scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve convincing individuals to invest in fake or non-existent cryptocurrency projects, with the promise of high returns.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Cloud mining scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve selling the idea of \"cloud mining,\" in which individuals can earn cryptocurrency by renting out the processing power of a remote server. However, these operations are often not legitimate and may not actually be mining cryptocurrency at all.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Pump and dump schemes</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve artificially inflating the price of a cryptocurrency through coordinated buying, in order to sell it at a higher price to unsuspecting buyers.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Ransomware scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve using malware to lock access to a device or system until a ransom is paid, often in cryptocurrency.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>ICO scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve fake initial coin offerings (ICOs), in which individuals are convinced to invest in a non-existent or fraudulent cryptocurrency project.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Social media scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve using social media platforms to promote fake or fraudulent cryptocurrency projects, or to trick individuals into giving away their personal and financial information. </p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Wallet scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve creating fake cryptocurrency wallet apps or websites, which may be used to steal individuals\' cryptocurrency assets.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Escrow scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve using fake escrow services to facilitate fraudulent cryptocurrency transactions.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Airdrop scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve fake airdrops, in which individuals are promised free cryptocurrency in exchange for their personal and financial information.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Code injection scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve injecting malicious code into legitimate cryptocurrency projects, which may be used to steal users\' assets or personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Exchange scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve fake or unregulated cryptocurrency exchanges, which may be used to steal users\' assets or personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Trading bot scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve selling fake or non-functional trading bots, which are supposed to automate the buying and selling of cryptocurrency.</p>\r\n\r\n        <li><strong>Malware scams</strong></li>\r\n        <p>These scams involve using malware to infect devices and steal cryptocurrency assets or personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n    </ol>\r\n    <br>\r\n    <p>It is important to be cautious and to do thorough research before investing in any cryptocurrency project or offering. By being aware of these and other types of scams, you can help to protect yourself and your assets from potential fraudulent activity.</p>', '4.webp', 'It can be helpful to be aware of the various types of scams that exist in the world of cryptocurrency. There are some common types of cryptocurrency scams.'),
('fa-question', 'What is the blockchain?', 'Blockchain - a tool with many purposes.', 5, 'blockchain', '<h2>What is the blockchain?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>\r\n    Blockchain is a distributed ledger technology that consists of a growing chain of blocks, or records, that hold information about transactions that have occurred online. Each block contains data encoded in a chronological manner, and these blocks are linked together in a way that makes it difficult to alter the data contained within them. The information stored in a blockchain is decentralized, meaning it is not stored in a single location, but rather is distributed across a network of computers. This makes it secure and resistant to tampering. Blockchain technology is used in a variety of applications, including the creation and transfer of cryptocurrency, supply chain management, and secure record-keeping.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What can be stored on blockchain?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>\r\n    The blockchain is a distributed database that allows for the storage of digital records, also known as blocks. These blocks can contain a variety of information, including financial transactions, contracts, identities, and other forms of data. Essentially, any type of information that can be represented in digital form can potentially be stored on the blockchain.\r\n</p>\r\n    \r\n<p>\r\n    One of the key characteristics of the blockchain is that it is decentralized, meaning that it is not controlled by any single entity or organization. Instead, it is maintained by a network of participating computers, also known as nodes, that validate and record transactions on the blockchain. This decentralized nature of the blockchain allows for the storage of information in a transparent and secure manner, as the data is replicated across the network and can only be modified with the consensus of the participating nodes.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    In addition to storing various types of data, the blockchain can also be used to support smart contracts, which are self-executing contracts with the terms of the agreement between buyer and seller being directly written into lines of code. These contracts can be used to automate a variety of processes and transactions, including financial transactions, supply chain management, and more.\r\n</p>', '5.webp', 'Blockchain is a distributed ledger technology that consists of a growing chain of blocks, or records, that hold information about transactions.'),
('fa-landmark', 'Blockchain vs Banks', 'Blockchain eliminates the need for middlemen.', 6, 'blockchain', '<h2>What are the benefits of the blockchain?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>Blockchain offer a number of benefits, including faster currency transfer speeds, lower transaction costs, reduced risk of manipulation by central governments, and global availability. </p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<li>One of the key features of the blockchain is that it allows for decentralized ownership and control of digital assets.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Each participant in the network has a copy of the database, which ensures the immutability of the data.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The blockchain is accessible to anyone with an internet connection and can be integrated into various apps and websites.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The blockchain maintains a public record of all balances and transactions that is available to anyone, rather than being restricted to a single company\'s systems.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Blockchain technology provides a secure and cost-effective method of sending payments that eliminates the need for third-party verification and reduces processing times compared to traditional bank transfers.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Security: The decentralized nature of the blockchain and the use of cryptography to secure transactions make it a secure platform for storing and transferring digital assets. Traditional banking systems, on the other hand, are more vulnerable to attacks and fraud.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>The lengthy processing times for traditional bank transfers, which can take up to three days to settle, are due to the complex nature of the current financial infrastructure. Bank transfers often have to pass through a series of intermediaries, such as correspondent banks and custodial services, before reaching their destination. This process involves reconciling the balances of the two banks across a global financial system that involves a wide range of traders, funds, asset managers, and other entities. This can be a logistical challenge for banks, as well as a inconvenience for consumers. Blockchain technology offers an alternative by providing a more efficient and secure way to transfer funds directly between parties, bypassing the need for intermediaries and reducing processing times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is difficult to predict whether or not crypto-currencies will completely replace traditional banking systems in the future. While crypto-currencies offer a number of benefits, such as faster transfer speeds, lower transaction costs, and increased security, they also have their own set of challenges and limitations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, crypto-currencies are still not widely accepted as a form of payment, and their value can be volatile due to market fluctuations. In addition, the regulatory landscape for crypto-currencies is still evolving, and there is a lack of clarity around how they will be treated by governments and financial authorities in the long term.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Given these challenges, it is likely that traditional banking systems will continue to play a significant role in the global economy, even if crypto-currencies gain wider adoption. It is possible that the two systems may coexist and interact with each other in various ways, rather than one completely replacing the other.</p>\r\n<br>', '6.webp', 'Blockchain offer a number of benefits, including faster currency transfer speeds, lower transaction costs, reduced risk of manipulation by central governments, and global availability.'),
('fa-question', 'What is an NFT?', 'NFTs gained popularity in 2020 and have continued to grow in popularity since then.', 7, 'ntf', '<p>NFT stands for non-fungible token, which is a digital item, such as a collectible avatar or a ticket, that is stored on the blockchain as a digital token. This token is unique and cannot be exchanged for an equal value like traditional fungible tokens, such as currency. For example, even if two NFTs have the same image, each token is unique and limited in number.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>The value of NFTs</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>NFTs have a value that is determined by the market, based on supply and demand. They can be bought and sold in the same way as physical assets, and they can represent both digital and physical items, such as artwork or real estate. Some users see tokenizing real-world assets in this way as a way to make buying, selling, and trading them more efficient, as well as potentially reducing the risk of fraud. NFTs provide a secure and transparent way to own and trade unique digital items.</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>How to create an NFT?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>To create an NFT, an artist or creator will first create a digital asset, such as a piece of art or a collectible. They will then use special software to create a unique digital token that represents ownership of that asset. This token is typically stored on a blockchain, such as Ethereum, which allows for the decentralized ownership and transfer of the asset.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>How do you buy NFTs?</h2>\r\n<p>To purchase an NFT, a buyer can use a cryptocurrency, such as Ether (ETH), to purchase the token from the creator or from a marketplace. Once the purchase is complete, the buyer becomes the owner of the digital asset and can do with it as they please, such as displaying it on their social media profile or selling it to someone else.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>NFT marketplaces</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<strong>OpenSea</strong>\r\n<p>Decentralized marketplace for buying and selling NFTs, including digital art, collectibles, and virtual real estate.</p>\r\n<strong>Rarible</strong>\r\n<p>Marketplace for buying and selling NFTs, including art, music, and other digital assets.</p>\r\n<strong>SuperRare</strong>\r\n<p>Marketplace for buying and selling digital art as NFTs</p>\r\n<strong>KnownOrigin</strong>\r\n<p>Marketplace for buying and selling digital art as NFTs, with a focus on contemporary and emerging artists.</p>\r\n<strong>Foundation</strong>\r\n<p>Marketplace for buying and selling digital art as NFTs, with a focus on established artists.</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>These are just a few examples, and there are many other NFT marketplaces available. Some marketplaces may specialize in certain types of NFTs, such as art or collectibles, while others may offer a more general selection of NFTs. It\'s important to do your research and choose a marketplace that meets your needs and has a good reputation.</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>Are NFTs cryptocurrency?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>While NFTs and cryptocurrencies share some similarities, they also have important differences. The main difference is that cryptocurrencies are fungible, meaning that one unit is interchangeable with another unit of the same type. NFTs, on the other hand, are non-fungible, meaning that each one is unique and cannot be exchanged for an equal value. For example, one Bitcoin is equal to another Bitcoin, but one NFT is not equal to another NFT. The value of an NFT is determined by market forces, such as supply and demand.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>Worth noting that the value of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) can vary widely, and not all NFTs are necessarily worth a significant amount. The value of an NFT is determined by a number of factors, including the rarity and uniqueness of the item, the perceived value of the item to collectors or enthusiasts, and the overall demand for the type of NFT in question. Some NFTs may be worth a significant amount due to these factors, while others may be worth very little.</p>\r\n<p>It\'s important to do your research and consider the value of an NFT carefully before purchasing one. While it is possible to make a profit by buying and selling NFTs, it is also possible to lose money if the value of an NFT decreases. As with any investment, there are risks involved, and it\'s important to be aware of those risks and to approach the market with caution.</p>\r\n<br>', '7.webp', 'The main difference is that cryptocurrencies are fungible, meaning that one unit is interchangeable with another unit of the same type.'),
('fa-book-skull', 'Cryptojacking or Cryptomining malware', 'Malicious websites could be using your CPU to mine cryptocurrencies.', 8, 'scams', '<h2>Cryptojacking definition</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Cryptojacking is the unauthorized use of someone\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency. It occurs when a website or other online service uses a person\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency without their knowledge or consent. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cryptomining code can run in the background on a victim\'s computer without their knowledge or consent. The victim may not be aware of the mining activity, but they may notice slower performance or delays in the execution of tasks. The cryptomining code can continue to operate while the victim uses their computer normally.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>How cryptojacking works</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li>A website or online service embeds code into their website or application that utilizes the processing power of a visitor\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency. This code can be activated as soon as the visitor loads the page or application.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The visitor\'s computer begins mining cryptocurrency in the background, while the visitor uses their computer normally. They may not be aware that their computer is being used to mine cryptocurrency.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The mined cryptocurrency is sent to the person or entity controlling the mining operation. They may use the cryptocurrency for their own purposes or sell it on an exchange.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>The affected user may notice a decrease in performance or delays in the execution of tasks on their computer, but they may not realize that this is due to cryptojacking.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Here are some stelis you can take to lirotect against cryptojacking</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Use antivirus or anti-malware software that includes protection against cryptocurrency mining. These programs can detect and block cryptocurrency mining scripts and other malicious code that may be used in cryptojacking attacks.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Install a browser extension that blocks cryptocurrency mining scripts. These extensions can help prevent your computer from being used to mine cryptocurrency without your knowledge or consent.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Enable javaScript blocking in your browser. Cryptocurrency mining scripts often rely on javaScript, so disabling it can help prevent your device from being used for mining.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Be cautious when visiting unfamiliar websites. Avoid clicking on links or downloading files from untrustworthy sources, as these may contain cryptocurrency mining code.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Keep your operating system and browser up to date. Installing updates can help protect against new threats, including those that may be used in cryptojacking attacks.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Maintain browser extensions. Some attackers use malicious browser extensions or exliloit legitimate extensions to run cryptocurrency mining scripts.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>By following these steps, you can help protect your computer from being used for cryptocurrency mining without your knowledge or consent.</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>What to do after you\'ve detected the cryptojacking and how to remove it.</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Disconnect your computer from the internet. This will prevent the cryptojacking malware from continuing to mine cryptocurrency and prevent it from communicating with the attacker\'s servers.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Run a scan with your antivirus or anti-malware software. These programs are designed to detect and remove malicious software, including cryptojacking malware. Follow the instructions provided by the software to remove the malware from your computer.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>If you were using a browser extension that was compromised or used to execute the cryptojacking malware, remove the extension from your browser.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>If the cryptojacking malware persists despite these steps, you may need to use a dedicated malware removal tool or seek help from a professional.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Once the cryptojacking malware has been removed, be sure to change any passwords and take other steps to secure your computer and protect against future attacks.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Reset operating system</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Cryptojacking involves the unauthorized use of a person\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency, without their knowledge or consent. While the main impact of this crime is the use of the victim\'s computing power, it is important to note that this is done for the benefit of criminals who are using the power to create cryptocurrency illicitly. The victim does not receive any benefit from the mining and may suffer a decrease in performance and an increase in energy consumption on their device. It is important to take steps to protect against cryptojacking and to be aware of the risks and consequences of this crime.</p>\r\n<br>', '8.webp', 'Cryptojacking involves the unauthorized use of a person\'s computer to mine cryptocurrency, without their knowledge or consent. '),
('fa-question', 'What is Ethereum', 'Ethereum has gained significant popularity as a cryptocurrency', 9, 'ethereum', '<h2>Ethereum has seen widespread adoption as a cryptocurrency in recent years, with its value currently hovering around 1100.</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>The Ethereum network is a platform for building decentralized applications, or apps that operate on a decentralized network rather than a single centralized server. This means that no individual person or entity has control over the application. Developers can create decentralized apps using Solidity, the programming language for Ethereum. Once an app is launched on the Ethereum network, it is run on thousands of decentralized machines called nodes, which ensure that the app functions as intended. Ethereum serves as the infrastructure for running these decentralized apps on a global scale, similar to how the Bitcoin network operates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ethereum is often referred to as a cryptocurrency, but it is more accurately described as a decentralized platform for building and running applications. While Ethereum does have its own digital currency, called Ether, the main purpose of the Ethereum platform is to enable the creation of decentralized applications, or apps that are not controlled by any single entity. The goal of Ethereum is to decentralize the internet by allowing developers to build applications that operate on a decentralized network rather than a single centralized server. This decentralized structure can provide increased security and resilience, as well as greater transparency and accountability.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another key feature of Ethereum is its use of a virtual machine, called the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM), which allows developers to build and deploy decentralized applications on the Ethereum platform. The EVM allows developers to write code in various programming languages, making it more accessible than other blockchain platforms that require developers to learn a proprietary language.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>In terms of its use as a digital currency, Ethereum has a number of advantages over other cryptocurrencies:</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Smart contracts: Ethereum enables the creation of smart contracts, which are self-executing contracts with the terms of the agreement between buyer and seller written directly into lines of code. These contracts can be used to automate a wide range of transactions and processes, making them more efficient and transparent.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Decentralized application platform: Ethereum is a decentralized platform for building and running applications, or dApps. This allows developers to create a wide range of decentralized applications that operate on a decentralized network rather than a single centralized server.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Wide programming language support: Ethereum\'s Virtual Machine (EVM) allows developers to write code in various programming languages, making it more accessible than other blockchain platforms that require developers to learn a proprietary language.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Fast transaction speeds: Ethereum has faster transaction speeds than many other cryptocurrencies, which makes it well-suited for applications that require fast and secure transactions.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Low fees: Ethereum has lower fees compared to many other cryptocurrencies, which makes it more cost-effective for applications that require frequent transactions.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Large developer community: Ethereum has a large and active developer community, which has helped it to attract a wide range of applications and use cases.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Active development ecosystem: Ethereum has an active development ecosystem, with regular updates and improvements to the platform. This helps to ensure that it remains relevant and well-suited to the needs of developers and users.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>Potential disadvantages of Ethereum:</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Scalability issues: Potential drawback of Ethereum is that its decentralized structure can make it challenging to handle a large volume of transactions, leading to slower speeds and higher fees for users. This is due to the decentralized nature of the platform, which can make it more difficult to scale and accommodate a large number of transactions.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Complexity: Ethereum is a more complex platform than some other cryptocurrencies, which can make it more difficult for new users to understand and use.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Lack of interoperability: Ethereum is its own independent platform, which means that it does not have built-in interoperability with other blockchain platforms. This can make it more difficult to use Ethereum in conjunction with other platforms or to transfer assets between platforms.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Regulation: Cryptocurrencies, including Ethereum, are often subject to regulatory uncertainty, which can create risks for investors and users.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Security vulnerabilities: Like any digital platform, Ethereum is vulnerable to security breaches and attacks. This can create risks for users and developers who rely on the platform.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Dependence on external factors: The demand for Ethereum can be influenced by investor sentiment, which can fluctuate based on a variety of factors. The regulatory environment for cryptocurrencies, including Ethereum, can impact their value and stability. Ethereum\'s value and stability can also be affected by broader market conditions, such as the overall state of the economy and investor confidence.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>Important to keep in mind that investing in Ethereum carries significant risks, including the possibility of losing all or part of your investment. It is important to carefully consider these risks before making any investment decisions.</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>Source: Trust me bro</p>\r\n<br>', '9.webp', 'Ethereum has seen widespread adoption as a cryptocurrency in recent years, with its value currently hovering around 1100.'),
('fa-question', 'What is a paper wallet?', 'Non-custodial cold storage wallet where you control the keys.', 10, 'wallet', '<h2>A paper wallet is a cold storage wallet that does not require an internet connection to function.\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>Paper wallet allows for offline transactions and balance monitoring, making it popular with businesspeople and investors who value security. Paper wallet is a physical document containing both a public and a private key, which are printed on the document.\r\nIt may also include a QR code that can be used to verify and sign transactions.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>Paper wallets are safe if you treat them as single-use wallets.</h2>\r\n\r\n<p> \r\nMeaning that you should only use the funds on a paper wallet once and then transfer any remaining balance to a new paper wallet or a more secure wallet. This helps to reduce the risk of someone finding and stealing the funds on the paper wallet.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paper wallets can be a secure way to store cryptocurrency, but they can also be inconvenient and difficult to use properly. This is because they require the use of an offline computer to generate the keys, and then the private keys must be imported into an online computer in order to spend the funds. This can be risky, as if the online computer is compromised, the funds on the paper wallet may be at risk of being stolen. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paper wallets can be a secure way to store cryptocurrency, but it is important to be cautious and avoid making mistakes when using them. This includes being diligent about checking for malware and being certain that the offline and online computers used to generate and access the keys are free from threats. It is also important to carefully follow all best practices when creating and using paper wallets, as a single mistake could compromise the security of the funds stored on them. While it may be inconvenient, it is better to take extra precautions and be thorough when it comes to the security of your cryptocurrency.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<br>', '10.webp', 'A paper wallet is a non-custodial cold storage wallet where you control the keys. It is offline, but other cold storage methods are now considered more secure.');
INSERT INTO `learn` (`class`, `h3`, `p`, `id`, `related_posts`, `html`, `image_name`, `meta`) VALUES
('fa-ranking-star', 'Paper wallet vs Hardware wallet', 'Storing a backup of your private key', 11, 'wallet', '<h2>The biggest difference</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>One key difference between using a hardware wallet and a paper wallet is the process of sending funds from the wallet. With a hardware wallet, the device signs the request to send funds and the private key never leaves the device. This adds an extra layer of security, as the private key is not exposed to any potentially compromised online devices.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a paper wallet, you must scan the private key and import it onto an online device in order to send funds. This means that the private key is now on an online device, which could potentially be less secure. As a result, it is important to be cautious and take extra precautions when using a paper wallet to ensure the security of your funds.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A paper wallet is primarily used as a backup for storing your private key, while a hardware wallet serves the same purpose but also allows you to authenticate transactions. With a hardware wallet, the only way to send from an address stored on the device is to confirm the transaction through the wallet itself. This added feature of transaction authentication provides an extra layer of security for your cryptocurrency.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>Paper wallets can be risky and inconvenient to use.</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    They are vulnerable to physical loss or theft and require secure generation and storage of keys. They also require the transfer of private keys to an online device in order to spend funds, which can be risky and time-consuming.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Overall, it is important to be cautious and follow best practices when using all wallets to ensure the security of the funds stored on them.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>', '11.webp', 'No matter which method you choose for storing your cryptocurrency, it is important to have a backup of the keys in case the original device or paper holding the key is lost or destroyed.'),
('fa-question', 'Types of blockchain', 'Exploring the Different Types of Blockchains', 12, 'blockchain', '<p>There are many different types of blockchains, including public and private chains, and those with different numbers and types of coins or tokens. It can be confusing to keep track of all the different blockchains, but understanding their features and characteristics can help you make informed decisions about which ones to use or invest in.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the most well-known blockchains:</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Bitcoin</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Ethereum</li>\r\n<br>\r\n<li>Ripple</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p> There are many other blockchains in existence, each with its own unique features and uses. The number of blockchains is continually growing as new ones are created.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<h2>There are four major types of Blockchain</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n<li><strong>Public blockchains:</strong></li>\r\n<p> \r\nDecentralized networks are open to anyone with a computer and internet connection. These networks do not have any restrictions on participation and allow anyone to join and contribute to the network. This is in contrast to private blockchains, which are restricted to a specific group or organization and may use a centralized authority for security.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Private blockchains:</strong></li>\r\n<p>Restricted networks that are only accessible to a specific group of people or organizations. These networks are \"permissioned,\" meaning that access is granted by the controlling entity and is generally limited to a smaller group of users. Private blockchains are often used by companies or organizations to store and manage data within a closed network, rather than relying on a public network.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Permissioned blockchains:</strong></li>\r\n<p>\r\n    Restricted networks that allow only certain groups or individuals to validate transactions or data within the network. These blockchains are often used in situations where high levels of privacy and security are required, as access to the network is strictly controlled.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    Permissioned and private blockchains are both restricted networks that are only accessible to a specific group of people or organizations. However, there are some key differences between the two types of blockchains:\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>Access control: Permissioned blockchains allow for some level of access to be granted to external parties, while private blockchains are completely closed off to outsiders.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Decentralization: Permissioned blockchains may be more decentralized than private blockchains, as they allow for the participation of external parties and may not be fully controlled by a single entity.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Security: Both permissioned and private blockchains offer increased security compared to public blockchains, as access is restricted. However, private blockchains may offer slightly higher security as they are completely closed off to outsiders and are fully controlled by a single entity.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li>Validation: Permissioned blockchains may use a centralized authority or a group of trusted nodes to validate transactions, while private blockchains are generally controlled by a single entity.</li>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Consortium blockchains:</strong></li>\r\n<p>Consortium or federated blockchains are decentralized networks that allow multiple members to collaborate and share data. This type of blockchain combines elements of both private and public blockchains, offering a blend of security and openness. </p>\r\n\r\n<p> One of the key features of consortium blockchains is that they allow multiple members to collaborate across a decentralized network. This can help to reduce the risks associated with private blockchains, which are controlled by a single entity and may be more vulnerable to attacks or fraud. Consortium blockchains also offer increased security compared to public blockchains, as access is restricted to a specific group of people or organizations.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<p> There are many different blockchains in existence, each with its own unique features and benefits. As a result, there is no one-size-fits-all answer to the question of which blockchain is the best to use. The best blockchain for your needs will depend on your specific requirements and use case.\r\nSome of the main factors to consider when choosing a blockchain include the level of security, privacy, and decentralization you need, as well as the type of applications or transactions you want to use the blockchain for. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> By carefully considering your needs and researching the different options available, you can choose the blockchain that is most suitable for your needs.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<br>', '12.webp', 'There are many blockchains in existence, each with its own unique features and uses. The number of blockchains is continually growing as new ones are created.'),
('fa-question', 'What is Ethereum 2.0?', 'Major upgrade to the Ethereum network', 13, 'ethereum', '<p>Ethereum is a blockchain platform that allows for the creation and execution of smart contracts, which are self-executing contracts with the terms of the agreement between buyer and seller being directly written into lines of code. Because Ethereum is decentralized and runs on a distributed ledger, it offers a level of security and transparency that is not possible with traditional online platforms, as it is immune to fraud and third-party interference.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ethereum was first conceptualized by Vitalik Buterin in 2013 and officially launched in 2015. Despite its initial success, Ethereum faced scalability issues as it was unable to process a high volume of transactions concurrently. Additionally, the Ethereum network was not energy-efficient, leading to the development of Ethereum 2.0, which aims to address these issues and improve the overall performance and sustainability of the network.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    Ethereum 2.0 aims to resolve the scalability and energy efficiency issues that were present in the original version of Ethereum. It accomplishes this through the implementation of a proof-of-stake (PoS) consensus algorithm, which allows for more transactions to be processed per second and makes the cryptocurrency more scalable. The transition to PoS also significantly reduces Ethereum\'s energy consumption by 99.95% and lowers transaction fees. These improvements make Ethereum 2.0 a more viable platform for large-scale applications and mainstream adoption.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n<h2>Could Ethereum 2.0 Beat Bitcoin?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<p> Bitcoin network can be slow compared to other cryptocurrencies, with transaction processing times and fees varying depending on network congestion. Ethereum has generally been able to process transactions more quickly than Bitcoin, although the Ethereum network has also experienced periods of high congestion and rising fees.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p> It is unlikely that Bitcoin will be able to match the capabilities of Ethereum, as the Ethereum network has established itself as a central player in the smart contract ecosystem with many protocols relying on or connecting to it. New protocols that attempt to challenge Ethereum\'s position may eventually find themselves integrating with or bridging to Ethereum in some way. As a result, Ethereum is likely to continue playing a dominant role in the smart contract space.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>', '13.webp', 'Ethereum was first conceptualized by Vitalik Buterin in 2013 and officially launched in 2015. Despite its initial success, Ethereum faced scalability issues as it was unable to process a high volume of transactions concurrently.'),
('fa-question', 'Types of cryptocurrencies', 'Several different types of cryptocurrencies in existence', 14, 'info', '<p>\r\n    Did you know that there are several different types of cryptocurrencies in existence? This article takes a closer look at the various types of cryptocurrencies and delves into their unique features and characteristics.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<li> <strong> Bitcoin </strong> </li>\r\n<p>Bitcoin is a well-known and highly respected cryptocurrency. It was the world\'s first cryptocurrency, with its origins traced back to a white paper published in 2008. It operates on a decentralized blockchain and is verified by a network of miners.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    The blockchain technology that underlies Bitcoin acts as a transparent and secure public record of all Bitcoin transactions. It enables the verification of ownership and helps to prevent fraud and unauthorized tampering with the currency. The decentralized nature of Bitcoin allows for fast and inexpensive peer-to-peer financial transactions, without the need for a third-party intermediary.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li> <strong> Ethereum </strong> </li>\r\n<p> Ethereum, also known as ETH, is the digital token used to facilitate transactions on the Ethereum platform. It serves as a means of compensation for participating nodes and can be traded on cryptocurrency exchanges. In addition to being bought and sold as a long-term investment, Ether is often used as a form of payment for goods and services or to access decentralized applications on the Ethereum networ.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li> <strong> Binance Coin </strong> </li>\r\n<p>Binance Coin (BNB) is the official cryptocurrency of the Binance exchange, the largest cryptocurrency exchange in the world as of 2023. Binance offers reduced transaction fees for users who pay with BNB, which has helped drive its adoption and make it one of the most valuable cryptocurrencies on the market. In order to maintain the value of BNB, Binance regularly \"burns\" a fixed percentage of the coins in circulation, effectively reducing the overall supply of BNB.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li> <strong> Tether </strong> </li>\r\n<p>Tether is a type of stablecoin, a cryptocurrency that is pegged to the value of a traditional fiat currency like the US dollar. The goal of Tether is to offer the advantages of cryptocurrency, like the elimination of intermediaries, while providing the stability of a government-issued currency, which is not subject to the same price volatility as many other cryptocurrencies.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li> <strong> Solana </strong> </li>\r\n<p>Solana is cryptocurrency that is native to the Solana platform, which uses blockchain technology similar to that of Ethereum and Bitcoin. One of the standout features of the Solana network is its high transaction speed, with the ability to process an impressive 50,000 transactions per second. This makes Solana an attractive choice for investors who prioritize speed in their trades.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li> <strong> USD Coin </strong> </li>\r\n<p>USD Coin is a stablecoin that is pegged to the value of the US dollar. Like Tether, it is built on the Ethereum blockchain. The goal of USD Coin is to create a \"fully digital\" version of the US dollar, one that can be used as a stable and convenient form of everyday money for online transactions, without the need for a bank account or geographic restrictions. It is not intended as an investment asset but rather as a means of exchange.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li> <strong> XRP </strong> </li>\r\n<p>XRP is a digital asset that is native to the Ripple network. It is used to facilitate cross-border payments and offers a faster and more affordable alternative to traditional money transfer methods. Ripple, the company behind XRP, has partnerships with various financial institutions and aims to provide solutions for banks and payment providers. XRP can be purchased on cryptocurrency exchanges and is also accepted as a form of payment on the Ripple network.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<li> <strong> Dogecoin </strong> </li>\r\n<p>Dogecoin, which was originally created as a joke about Bitcoin, has become a widely recognized and valuable cryptocurrency. It was founded in 2013 and was inspired by a popular dog meme from that year. Dogecoin gained significant attention in 2021 and has a market value of 8.4 billion euros as of October 2022. It is based on blockchain technology and was forked from Litecoin. Unlike Bitcoin, Dogecoin has no set limit on the number of coins that can be mined. This means that anyone can mine an unlimited amount of Dogecoins, but it also means that there is a higher risk of the value of Dogecoin declining due to the potentially infinite supply. Dogecoin can be bought and sold on cryptocurrency exchanges and is also used for transactions on the Dogecoin network.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>', '14.webp', ' Did you know that there are several different types of cryptocurrencies in existence? This article takes a closer look at the various types of cryptocurrencies and delves into their unique features and characteristics.'),
('fa-ranking-star', 'Top 3 Bitcoin Whales', 'Who is the largest owner of Bitcoin, and what is a Bitcoin whale?', 15, 'info', '<h2>What is crypto whale?</h2>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>An individual or group who holds a significant amount of cryptocurrency is referred to as a \"crypto whale.\" These major players in the market have the ability to influence the price of a particular cryptocurrency due to their large size and ownership. The term \"crypto whale\" is often used to describe those who hold large amounts of Bitcoin, but it can also be applied to those who hold large amounts of other cryptocurrencies. \"Crypto whale\" is similar to the term \"Bitcoin whale,\" which is used to describe a major player in the market with the ability to significantly influence the price of an asset.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li><strong>Satoshi Nakamoto</strong></li>\r\n  <p>Satoshi Nakamoto is the pseudonym used by the creator(s) of Bitcoin. The true identity of the person or group behind this pseudonym remains unknown. Nakamoto is believed to hold a significant amount of Bitcoin, estimated to be over 1 million BTC. No transactions have been linked to Nakamoto\'s wallet, and their true identity remains a mystery to this day. Despite the anonymity surrounding the identity of Nakamoto, they are a significant figure in the world of cryptocurrency due to their creation of Bitcoin.\r\n  </p>\r\n  \r\n  <li><strong>Elon Musk</strong></li>\r\n  <p>In 2021, Tesla, a company owned by Elon Musk, was known to hold approximately 33,000 Bitcoins. However, it is believed that the company has since sold off some of its Bitcoin holdings in order to generate revenue. A report released by Tesla states that the company currently holds approximately $218 million worth of digital assets on its balance sheet. It is unclear from the report whether these digital assets are all Bitcoin or if they include other cryptocurrencies as well.\r\n  </p>\r\n  \r\n  <li><strong>Vitalik Buterin</strong></li>\r\n  <p>Vitalik Buterin published the Ethereum white paper in November 2013 and later launched the cryptocurrency at a conference in Miami in January 2014. He was assisted in this launch by co-founders Charles Hoskinson, Gavin Wood, Anthony Di Iorio, and Joseph Lubin. Buterin has reportedly made the most out of the co-founders through his involvement in Ethereum, with an estimated net worth of around 290,000 ETH, or approximately $363 million as of January 2023.</p>\r\n</ol>  \r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '15.webp', 'A \"crypto whale\" is a term used to describe an individual or group that holds a large amount of a particular cryptocurrency. These individuals or groups are sometimes referred to as \"whales\" because they have the ability to significantly influence the market for a particular cryptocurrency due to their large size and ownership.'),
('fa-book-skull', 'How wallets get hacked?', 'Different types of threats that exist and what measures need to be taken to prevent them', 16, 'wallet', '    <p>It is well known that the security of your cryptocurrency depends on the type of wallet you use. However, even the most secure wallet cannot protect against all threats. The only way to truly secure your cryptocurrency is to understand the different types of threats that exist and what measures need to be taken to prevent them.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n    <p>In this section, we will discuss the methods that hackers may use to access your wallet and the steps you can take to prevent them from doing so.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n \r\n    \r\n    <br>\r\n    <h2>How Hackers Can Access Your Wallet?</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <li><strong>Malware</strong></li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <p>Hackers are using various types of malware to target popular operating systems like Windows and macOS. Some of these viruses are designed to detect when a cryptocurrency address is copied and replace it with a wallet address belonging to the hacker. If this substitution is successful, the cryptocurrency is sent to the hacker\'s controlled address instead of its intended destination.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n      <p>Mars Stealer is a prevalent type of malware that has been upgraded from a trojan from 2019. It targets over 40 browser cryptocurrency wallets and has the ability to steal a user\'s private keys. This wallet-stealing malware is spread through various online channels, such as file-hosting websites, torrent clients, and other nefarious download sites. It targets the file on a user\'s device that stores private keys, steals the information, and removes any trace of the theft.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n    <br>\r\n    <li><strong>Phishing Attacks</strong></li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <p>Phishing attacks are a common tactic used by hackers to steal information. In these attacks, the hacker creates fake websites that closely resemble legitimate cryptocurrency platforms in order to trick targets. The attackers may also use misleading domain names, such as using \"trezor.co\" instead of \"trezor.io\", in order to deceive people.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n    <p>These fake websites are often indistinguishable from the legitimate ones, making it easy for targets to be fooled into logging in with their cryptocurrency account credentials. Once the victim inputs this information, it is transferred to the hackers. The hackers can then use this information to access the victim\'s actual account on the legitimate cryptocurrency website.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n    <br>\r\n    <li><strong>Fake Hardware Wallets</strong></li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <p>Hackers may steal cryptocurrency through fake hardware wallets by selling counterfeit hardware wallets that look genuine but lack the same level of security. They may also use phishing attacks to trick victims into sending money for a fake hardware wallet. Additionally, malware can be used to infect a device and gain access to a hardware wallet, allowing the hacker to steal the cryptocurrency stored in it. To protect against these types of attacks, it is important to only purchase hardware wallets from reputable sources and to be aware of phishing attempts. Keeping your device and antivirus software up to date can also help prevent malware infections.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n    <p>In 2020, the hardware wallet company Ledger experienced a data breach. Scammers have taken advantage of this by sending fake hardware wallets to people whose data was obtained through a third-party data breach. These fake wallets contain hardware that is meant to steal the user\'s cryptocurrency. The scam, which first emerged in May, involves the scammers mailing packages to Ledger users containing a fake Ledger Nano wallet. The fake wallet has a flash drive soldered onto the inside and the package includes a sealed bag with Ledger\'s logo and shrink-wrapping to make it appear unopened.\r\n    </p>\r\n    \r\n    <br>\r\n    <li><strong>SMS 2FA Verification Exploits</strong></li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <p>SMS two-factor authentication (2FA) verification exploits are a type of attack that can be used to gain unauthorized access to a cryptocurrency wallet. In these attacks, the hacker may use a variety of techniques to intercept the SMS message containing the 2FA code, allowing them to log in to the victim\'s wallet without their knowledge. To protect against SMS 2FA verification exploits, it is recommended to use a different method of 2FA, such as an authenticator app or a hardware token, instead of relying solely on SMS messages. It is also important to use strong, unique passwords and to enable 2FA on all accounts that offer it.</p>\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    \r\n    <br>\r\n     <h2>Tips for Preventing Theft:</h2>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Keep your operating system and antivirus software up to date: Installing updates and using the latest version of your operating system and antivirus software can help protect against known malware threats.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Be cautious when clicking links or downloading files: Avoid clicking on links or downloading files from unknown sources or websites. If you receive an email or message from an unfamiliar sender, do not click on any links or download any attachments.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n     <li>\r\n        Avoid storing private key information in a format that can be easily stolen, such as plain text. Be careful when copying and pasting password information to prevent it from being intercepted by a third party.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Enable two-factor authentication: Two-factor authentication (2FA) adds an extra layer of security by requiring you to provide a second form of identification in addition to your password when logging in to an account.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n    <li>Avoid accessing sensitive information on public networks: Public Wi-Fi networks are vulnerable to hacking and should be avoided when accessing sensitive information. Use a virtual private network (VPN) to encrypt your internet connection when using public networks.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n   \r\n    \r\n     <li>\r\n        Close your web browser after completing each transaction to prevent unauthorized access to your account.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n     <li>\r\n        Be vigilant for suspicious links to wallet websites and apps and carefully review transactions and approvals in your cryptocurrency wallet to ensure they are legitimate.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <br>\r\n    \r\n   \r\n    <br>', '16.webp', 'It is well known that the security of your cryptocurrency depends on the type of wallet you use. However, even the most secure wallet cannot protect against all threats.');

